peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: The best way to determine its worth is to bring it to a professional antique furniture appraiser who has specific knowledge of antique furniture pieces and knows all the period, material and style details that impact its value.
peopleAlsoAsk.title: How Much is Your Antique Furniture Worth? | Appraisal Guide

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How can you tell if a kitchen table is antique?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Look at the table closely to see if there are different types of wood. The more variation you can see, the more likely it is to be an antique. Similarly, try to find any irregular dovetailing where two pieces of wood join - often a sign of hand-made craftsmanship, rather than mass-produced designs.

peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: End tables are typically larger and come in pairs, while side tables are smaller and stand-alone.
